  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">FFD - Feelings of Reality - ID</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cinema is a powerful tools to convey specific messages for specific purposes. Thus, we intend to use the medium to convey messages on disability rights awareness. As a festival we have been receiving regular submission of  film about disabilities. We have also had some programs that focus on that issue. In this project, we aim to enhance the effect/impact of the films about disability throughVR documentary production. VR cinema has a powerful strength on bringing the reality closer to audience. In addition to telling thestories of our difabel friends, we also would like to invite the audience to feel their reality.

We planned to conduct researches in the selected regions in order to map the disability rights problem and the needs to open a path to advocacy through some FGDs. After we have gathered the data, then the production phase will commence. It begins with the VR filmmaking workshops with the invited experts, to teach our selected mentors about the basic of VR filmmaking. The mentor then proceed to teach and facilitate the VR documentary production to our selected young filmmakers. Here, we will try to portray the feeling of our difabel friends through the lens of VR documentary.

The next step is the exhibition process, that will be held inour film festival. After we have produced the VR documentary, we want to deliver the feelings we have obtained in the production phase to the audience. Here we are planning to invite all the disability rights communities/organisations, stakeholders, decision makers, activists, and of course the general audience of our festival to experience the feelings we have captured in the VR documentary.

We hope that through the heightened experience of VR documentary, we also receive different degree of awarenessand special attention to the disability issue. The feelings of reality can be a starting point to give insight on the feelings of difabel people. And by exposing this tech and form of documentary to the public, a further production on this issue with thistech can be attained; thus building the larger impact to call for immediate response/action.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="90">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Forum Film Dokumenter (FFD) focusing on the development of documentary film as a medium of expression and ecosystem of knowledge, through exhibition, education, and archiving. We sought to explore the raw potential in Indonesia#s cinema: the documentary medium. Certain traits differentiate documentary films from other audiovisual products, a significant place as a media that educates, reflective, transcends time and space, Amidst the strong current of the mass media, documentary films hold its own role as independent, aspirational media.  Since initiated in 2002, our organisation consistently organize the very first documentary film festival in Southeast Asia: Festival Film Dokumenter. In this festival we always try to observe certain social issues as its focus, as well as creating bridge between documentary filmmakers, professional filmmakers, and the general audiences on the purpose of improving the quality and quantity of Indonesian documentary films.

The presence of our organisation has had an impact on the public awareness of the documentary film in Indonesia, especially in Java. Since then, the production of documentary film has gradually increased from only 35 films in 2002, to 177 films in 2017. It can also be seen from the growth of our festival audience, from only 1903 people were comingin 2015, the number has increased to 2579 audiences in last 2017.</narrative>
